item.title: Nicotine
item.dc:creator: @RUNE-PK RUNE-PK
item.description:
@RUNE-PK wrote:

[quote=“Skyro, post:4, topic:542672”][quote=http://www.wisegeek.com/what-is-nicotine-poisoning.htm]
If exposure continues, more serious symptoms such as vomiting and trouble breathing could occur. Eventually, if acute nicotine poisoning develops, it could cause seizures, fainting, coma or even death in some cases. Most of the time, a person can recover with no lasting effects, but prompt medical attention is usually a good idea.
[/quote][/quote]

Thanks Skyro!
